Whoo!
Good job.

00:23.076 --> 00:24.243
Great job.

00:26.346 --> 00:28.280
It is my sincere hope
that this center

00:28.348 --> 00:30.282
will become a beacon
of academic excellence

00:30.350 --> 00:33.219
in an underserved community
for years to come.

00:33.286 --> 00:34.720
Clara, would you do
the honors, please?

00:34.788 --> 00:35.955
Of course.

00:38.024 --> 00:38.991
Thank you,
Mrs. Musso,

00:39.059 --> 00:40.693
for your friendship
and generosity.

00:40.761 --> 00:42.328
You're welcome, governor.

00:49.169 --> 00:50.336
Thank you, ladies.

00:51.738 --> 00:54.206
For many years,
and I speak to you today

00:54.274 --> 00:55.608
not as a politician

00:55.675 --> 00:58.911
but along with my wife
as parents.

00:58.979 --> 01:00.546
Public education in America

01:00.614 --> 01:01.914
has been in peril.

01:01.982 --> 01:06.218
You know the refrain... lack of
funds, underqualified teachers,

01:06.286 --> 01:07.753
negligent parents.

01:07.821 --> 01:12.291
And to this I say,
no more excuses.

01:22.068 --> 01:23.936
The guy in the denim
jacket... do we know him?

01:24.004 --> 01:25.404
...Vote
for accountability.

01:25.472 --> 01:28.107
Cast your vote for...
Denim jacket. 11:00.

01:28.175 --> 01:31.177
...Vote for this
great state of Virginia.

01:31.244 --> 01:33.078
Governor,
your car's waiting.

01:34.714 --> 01:36.782
Thank you, kind voters
of Virginia.

01:43.657 --> 01:44.857
Thanks very much
for coming out.

01:44.925 --> 01:46.392
Appreciate the support.
Thank you.

01:46.459 --> 01:48.527
Thanks very much for your help.

01:48.595 --> 01:49.695
Thanks very much
for your support.

01:49.763 --> 01:51.030
It's nice to see you today.

01:51.097 --> 01:53.265
Great to see you.
Thanks very much for your support.

01:53.333 --> 01:54.934
Let's go get them.

01:55.001 --> 01:56.502
Let's get out and vote, huh?

01:56.570 --> 01:58.237
Thanks for your support.

01:58.305 --> 01:59.772
Thank you for the support.

02:03.643 --> 02:04.910
Thanks for coming today.

02:15.622 --> 02:17.256
The governor's down.
He's hit.

02:33.373 --> 02:35.841
There's no such thing
as an "assassin's gaze."

02:35.909 --> 02:37.476
All right.
So I can report back

02:37.544 --> 02:39.945
that you can't tell if Duane
Corey was acting alone.

02:40.013 --> 02:41.347
Didn't
say that.

02:41.414 --> 02:42.348
No, he had an accomplice.

02:42.415 --> 02:44.116
It was the governor.

02:44.184 --> 02:45.751
What? Come on.

02:45.819 --> 02:47.519
I know. It turns your
stomach, doesn't it?

02:47.587 --> 02:48.888
The governor
knew Michelle daly.

02:48.955 --> 02:51.490
Of course he knew her.
She was a staffer.

02:51.558 --> 02:55.094
No, he "knew" knew her.
Know what I mean?

02:55.161 --> 02:58.731
Flirtatious,
flared nostrils, admiring look.

02:58.798 --> 03:00.266
Yeah,
she really fancied him.

03:00.333 --> 03:01.600
The FBI is
paying you to find out

03:01.668 --> 03:02.768
if the governor
was acting alone,

03:02.836 --> 03:04.470
not dig into the
governor's personal life.

03:04.537 --> 03:06.071
No, the FBI's paying me
to poke around

03:06.139 --> 03:07.006
and, you know, find the truth.

03:07.073 --> 03:09.708
I'm not a glorified cop, Ben.

03:09.776 --> 03:11.310
Foster, show Reynolds
the situation.

03:11.378 --> 03:12.878
The governor's in a tight race.

03:12.946 --> 03:14.013
Too close to call.

03:14.080 --> 03:16.382
A staffer who was
clearly more than that

03:16.449 --> 03:17.483
was shot dead.

03:17.550 --> 03:18.851
Now the man's
back up in the polls.

03:18.919 --> 03:20.219
You can't ignore the possibility

03:20.287 --> 03:23.088
that the girl was just a victim
of a 9-point bullet bump.

03:24.491 --> 03:25.424
Where
are you going?

03:25.492 --> 03:26.625
To see the governor.

03:26.693 --> 03:29.094
Cal, listen.
Brooks isn't just any old governor.

03:29.162 --> 03:32.097
I know. He's a close and
personal friend of yours.

03:32.165 --> 03:34.767
I appreciate this must
be difficult for you.

03:34.834 --> 03:36.769
As the majority stakeholder
in this firm...

03:36.836 --> 03:40.639
see, I bet that you regret
saying that already.

03:40.707 --> 03:43.142
Just go easy on him.

03:43.209 --> 03:45.244
Ok? I respect
this man a lot.

03:45.312 --> 03:47.947
Someday he could be president.

03:48.014 --> 03:50.182
Not with this girl's blood
on his hands, he won't.

03:50.183 --> 03:55.083
